[normal]Written evidence submitted by [bold]Linkage Community Trust[bold]Summary[bold]Although Linkage Community Trust are not aware of any of our own service users being particularly affected by housing costs in the reformed welfare system, we are conscious that the impacts on vulnerable people with learning disabilities and th
[normal]eir families who live in social housing are being felt far and wide across the country.
[normal]We have become aware of several initiatives which are being used to support vulnerable people to afford to stay in their homes. These initiatives are outlined in more d
[normal]etail in our full response. 
[normal]They clearly highlight the resistance from front-line workers and Local Authorities to the incoming welfare changes, which are seemingly proving more costly to implement and enforce than the previous system. 
[normal]&#xa0;
