[normal]3. Our own experiences[bold]3.1 
[normal]Linkage Community Trust had one service user who moved into a 2-bedroom property in February 2013 as he required sleep-in staff due to his needs. The recent changes to 
[normal]housing benefits may have affected him but, due to staff incurring extra utility costs, Linkage only charged this service user the 1-bedro
[normal]om rent fee to compensate this.
[normal]Although most of our service users live in 1-bedroom properties, we are anticipating t
[normal]hat those service users in 2-bed accommodation may be affected by the changes to housing-related benefits in the near future as they are re-assessed for housing benefits. This is because their current housing benefi
[normal]ts applications are historical.
